<p><font face="Arial Black"><font color="#000000"><font size=+3>Using Patterns
in Hypermedia Applications</font></font></font></center>

<p><font size=+3>• The key is experience in hypermedia applications design</font>
<br><font size=+3>• Hypermedia design patterns&nbsp; help capture and reuse
the experience</font>
<br><font size=+3>• Patterns: reusing the navigation, interaction and interface
structure of hypermedia applications</font>
<br><font size=+3>• Help to organize the navigational structure in such
a way that we can provide the user with comfortable navigation spaces in
which he will not get lost and will not experience cognitive overhead</font>
<br><font size=+3>• Some patterns discovered</font>
<br><font size=+2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; – Navigational Context</font>
<br><font size=+2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; – News</font>
<br><font size=+2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; – Landmark</font>
<br><font size=+2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; – Information on Demand</font>
